Block Macros from Running in Office Files from the Internet	Enabled	MUSR_MQADMIN : Value Not Found		Prevents execution of VBA macros in Office documents downloaded from the internet (Mark-of-the-Web).	1) Open Group Policy Management Console (GPMC) 2) Edit applicable User GPO 3) Navigate to: User Configuration → Administrative Templates → Microsoft Office → Security Settings 4) Enable "Block macros from running in Office files from the Internet" 5) Apply and link the GPO Registry (for audit reference): HKCU\Software\Policies\Microsoft\Office\16.0\Common\Security\blockcontentexecutionfrominternet = 1	• Run gpresult /r → confirm GPO applied • Check registry value = 1 • Open a downloaded macro-enabled file → macros blocked automatically	If disabled, attackers can deliver malicious macro-enabled documents via phishing emails, leading to remote code execution, malware deployment, credential theft, and lateral movement.
Disable All Macros without Notification	Enabled	MUSR_MQADMIN : Value Not Found		All VBA macros shall be disabled without user notification to eliminate social-engineering based macro execution	1) Open Group Policy Management Console (GPMC) 2) Edit applicable User GPO 3) Navigate to: User Configuration → Administrative Templates → Microsoft Office → Security Settings 4) Enable "Disable all macros without notification" 5) Apply and link the GPO Registry (for audit reference): HKCU\Software\Policies\Microsoft\Office\16.0\Common\vbawarnings = 4	• Run gpresult /r → confirm GPO applied • Check registry value = 4 • Open a downloaded macro-enabled file → macros blocked automatically	Allowing macro prompts enables users or administrators to unknowingly execute malicious code, leading to server compromise and persistence.
